7nm process. AMD went directly from 12nm, stride meteor directly to 7nm. You know, Intel's 10nm is still difficult to produce, it is said that Intel's 14nm process will be used in 2021. It is enough to prove how powerful the latest AMD 3 generation Ryzen series processors are!

fields.title: New Intel Core 10th Generation CPUs coming soon
fields.content:
Intel has also launched new Core series logos, including Core i7, Core i5, Core i3, which are completely different from the past, and have become square and completely flat. The background has been changed to neatly arranged small squares and black and white gradients. Transition, including Intel LOGO. Since the 65nm Merom first-generation Core in 2006, each major upgrade of Intel Core will bring a new image logo, and the style will gradually transition from early three-dimensional and round to flat and sharp, but the classic blue tone is cancelled and the black and white tone is changed the first time.

It is reported that Intel's 10th-generation desktop processors are scheduled to be released next month. Before that, only the specifications of some 10th-generation processors had flowed out on the network. Recently, the information of the 10th-generation processors without a nuclear display was also leaked. In this way, 10 The information about the desktop CPU generation has basically been leaked. From the relevant information, there are currently known 4 i9 processors, 4 i7 processors, 6 i5 processors and 3 i3 processors.

The suffix with the letter "F" stands for without a nuclear display. There are 6 types of such CPUs, including 2 i9 processors, 2 i7 processors, and 2 i5 processors. From the specifications, the "F" The specifications of the CPU without the "F" are the same, but the price is definitely cheaper with the "F". The i3 does not have the information of the "F" processor yet, but considering the existence of the previous i3-9100F , This generation of i3 should also have similar products.

The shortcomings of the 10th generation CPU are mainly that it continues to use the 14nm process, and its performance in terms of energy consumption is not as good as that of rival AMD. It is said that its highest-end i9-10900K consumes more than 300W, and it uses the new LGA 1200 interface, which requires the latest 400 series. Chipset motherboard, so old users can't upgrade smoothly, which will increase the upgrade cost of users, which is not as good as AMD.

According to the price information circulated on the Internet, the price of the 10th generation processor will not increase significantly compared to the 9th generation, and will basically remain at the same level. Combined with the current advantages of AMD, the reliability of the news is still very high However, the price of the new 400 series motherboards may be more expensive than the previous generation motherboards at the initial stage of the listing, so the installation cost will still be higher than the 9th generation. However, these are not yet determined. The specific news will not be determined until it is released, so users who want to assemble a new machine must continue to wait.

fields.title: AMD releases third-generation Ryzen processors, outperforming Intel
fields.content:
On May 27, 2019, AMD officially released its third-generation Ryzen processor product at the Taipei Computer Show. See what excels at this third-generation Ryzen.

The third generation of Ryzen adopts the third-generation Ryzen processor of the new Zen 2 architecture. The IPC has increased by about 15%, the cache has been doubled directly, and the floating-point computing performance has been doubled. The entire system also uses TSMC. The 7nm FinFET process is the world's first 7nm CPU.

The main product is the R7 3700X. It has 8 cores and 16 threads, the base frequency is 3.6GHz, the maximum boost frequency is 4.4GHz, and it has 36MB of total cache. While benchmarking the I7-9700K, the power consumption is only exaggerated. 65W TDP, it seems that TSMC's 7nm FinFET process has greatly improved.

Then came the R7 3800X. Like the R7 3700X, it also has 8 cores and 16 threads. The basic master rate is 3.9GHz, the automatic boost frequency (Boost) is 4.5GHz, 36MB total cache, and the power consumption comes to 105W TDP. The benchmark product For Intel's i9-9900K.

The last appearance is the third-generation Ryzen processor's high-end product R9 3900X, which has a powerful 12-core 24 threads, the basic frequency is 3.8GHz, and the automatic boost (Boost) is 4.6GHz. The cache and power consumption are only 105W TDP, which can be said to exceed the benchmark Intel i9-9920X.
